<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2000-10-13a.57.0" nospeaker="true" colnum="57"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld199900/ldhansrd/vo001013/text/01013w01.htm#01013w01_wqn0">
	Consular Representation
</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2000-10-13a.57.1" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/lord/100550" speakername="Lord Roper" colon="" colnum="57"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld199900/ldhansrd/vo001013/text/01013w01.htm#01013w01_wqn0">
	<p pid="a.57.1/1">asked Her Majesty's Government:</p>
	<p pid="a.57.1/2" qnum="HL4036">In which of those member states of the Council of Europe whose citizens require a British visa there is no British embassy or consular representative; and what plans they have to establish embassies in such countries.</p>
</ques>

<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2000-10-13a.57.2" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/lord/100574" speakername="Baroness Scotland of Asthal" colon=":" colnum="57"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld199900/ldhansrd/vo001013/text/01013w01.htm#01013w01_spmin0">
	<p pid="a.57.2/1">The only country which falls into this category is Moldova. The Foreign and Commonwealth Office is considering in its annual budgeting round how best to use the resources obtained in the 2000 spending review to enhance its network of posts to deliver its objectives and public service agreement. The case for a post in Moldova will be considered in this context.</p>
</reply>

